</code></pre> <ol> <li>When the <code>Eventlinker.on</code> method is used as a context manager via the <code>with</code> statement, it allows multiple    callbacks to be associated with events within the <code>linkage context block</code>, defining the event workflow.</li> </ol> <pre><code>from pyventus import EventLinker

def event_callback() -&gt; str:
    print("Event received!")
    return "Event succeeded!"

async def success_callback(msg: str) -&gt; None:
    print(msg)

def failure_callback(exc: Exception) -&gt; None:
    print(exc)


EventLinker.subscribe(
    "StringEvent", event_callback=event_callback, success_callback=success_callback, failure_callback=failure_callback,
)
